        "created_at": "2026-02-11T14:09:44.516Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Managing audio during calls, especially group calls, can be difficult, especially when mobile in a car or on a bike, or when wearing winter clothes. I propose adding a programmatic API or system-level shortcut to mute/unmute Signal calls instantly, even when the phone isnt in hand or the screen is off.</p>\n<p>This would allow group call members to mute/unmute without fumbling with the app ui, and allow a physical mute button to mute/unmute a call via bluetooth</p>\n<p>Best workaround Ive found on iOS is Voice Control, which isnt reliable: app has to be front, the os has to clearly understand the user (often doesnt work the first time) Voice Control needs to be enabled, etc</p>\n<p>Suggested implementation would be to expose a secure broadcast intent (Android) or shortcut action (iOS) to toggle call mute state, and something similar to get the current mute state, it could be opt-in and require user permission. note: Im not familiar with android as much so Im not sure what would offer the same level of control as shortcuts.</p>",
